fields.name: Appetizers
fields.details: Small dishes served before the main course to stimulate the appetite.

fields.name: Soups
fields.details: Hot liquid food made by boiling ingredients such as meat, vegetables, or fish in stock or water.

fields.name: Salads
fields.details: Cold dishes of raw or cooked vegetables, typically seasoned with oil, vinegar, or other dressing.

fields.name: Main Courses
fields.details: The primary dish in a meal consisting of several courses.

fields.name: Seafood
fields.details: Edible aquatic animals, excluding mammals, including fish, mollusks, and crustaceans.

fields.name: Vegetarian
fields.details: Dishes that do not contain meat, fish, or poultry.

fields.name: Vegan
fields.details: Dishes that do not contain any animal products or by-products.

fields.name: Pasta
fields.details: Italian dishes made with dough of flour, eggs, and water, formed into various shapes and typically cooked in boiling water.

fields.name: Pizza
fields.details: Italian dish consisting of a flat round base of dough baked with toppings.

fields.name: Desserts
fields.details: Sweet food eaten at the end of a meal.

fields.name: Beverages
fields.details: Any type of drink other than water.

fields.name: Asian Cuisine
fields.details: Food from countries such as China, Japan, Korea, Vietnam, and Thailand.

fields.name: Mediterranean
fields.details: Food from countries bordering the Mediterranean Sea, particularly Greece, Italy, and Spain.

fields.name: American
fields.details: Traditional and contemporary food from the United States.

fields.name: Breakfast
fields.details: Food items typically eaten in the morning as the first meal of the day.
